UN Secretary General Kofi Annan expressed deep concern over Nepal's political turmoil, urging a return to democracy after King Gyanendra dismissed the coalition government and imposed a state of emergency.
The US and EU echoed these sentiments, calling for the restoration of multiparty democracy.
Japan voiced concern over the power grab and urged the release of detained political leaders.
India's ties with Nepal remain strong despite China's neutrality.
The region faces instability as Nepal grapples with political dysfunction and a longstanding Maoist insurgency.
King Gyanendra aims to restore democracy through a new Cabinet and peace talks with rebels.
